Statistical Inference
- processs of using a sample to make conclusions of a wider population
- population: collection of all individuals
- sample: randomly selected subset from pop
- point estimate: numeric computation using sample
  + sample statistic/ statistic
- population parameter: a fixed, numerical value that describes an entire group or statistical population


