Sampling distribution: probability distribution of a specific sample statistic calculated from random samples of the same size drawn from a single population 


bootstrapping: resampling technique used to estimate the accuracy of a sample statistic by repeatedly drawing samples from it with replacement
- randomly draw a single observation from the original sample (drawn from population
- record observation's value
- return observation to original sample
- repeat above the same number of times as there are observations in original sample (eg. sample size = 50, bootstrap sample = 50)


- bootstrap = sample of same size, true sampling = sample of original size








